# Frontend Conventions

## Stack

- Vanilla JS, no framework, no jQuery, no build step (browser loads
  `static/js/*.js` directly as ES modules).
- Files: `audio.js`, `game.js`, `socket.js`, `ui.js`, plus `sw.js`
  service worker.

## `globalThis` over `window` / `self`

Prefer `globalThis` everywhere — it works in browsers, service workers,
and tests under Node. Sonar will flag `window.X` and `self.X` as
`javascript:S7764`.

```js
// ❌ BAD
window.location.href = '/';
self.addEventListener('install', ...);

// ✅ GOOD
globalThis.location.href = '/';
globalThis.addEventListener('install', ...);
```

## WebSocket message handlers

`socket.js` keeps handlers as **named top-level functions** plus a flat
`MESSAGE_HANDLERS` map. Don't inline them into the `ws.onmessage`
closure — that pushes cognitive complexity over Sonar's 15 limit.

```js
function onChatMessage(m) { /* ... */ }
function onRoomDissolved(m) { /* ... */ }

const MESSAGE_HANDLERS = {
    chat: onChatMessage,
    room_dissolved: onRoomDissolved,
    /* ... */
};

ws.onmessage = (event) => {
    const msg = JSON.parse(event.data);
    const handler = MESSAGE_HANDLERS[msg.type];
    if (handler) handler(msg);
};
```

## Jest under WSL — use Docker

`npm test` from a WSL prompt fails because the Windows-side `npm`
resolves the workspace as a UNC path. Always run tests through Docker:

```bash
docker run --rm -v "$PWD:/work" -w /work node:20-alpine \
  sh -c "npm ci --silent && npm test -- --coverage \
         --coverageReporters=lcov --coverageDirectory=coverage-js"
```

The lcov output is used by Sonar (`sonar.javascript.lcov.reportPaths`).

## Accessibility

- Use `<button type="button">` for clickable controls — never
  `<a role="button">`. Sonar `Web:S6819`.
- Every `<label>` must have `for="..."` pointing to its control's `id`.
- Add `aria-label` to `<aside>`, `<section>`, and icon-only buttons.

## CDN scripts

`canvas-confetti` loads from a CDN. The game must **not** crash if the
CDN is blocked — `fireConfetti()` in `socket.js` wraps the call in a
`typeof confetti !== 'function'` guard plus `try/catch`.
